cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on generating 3D shapes using neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of Adaptive Instance Normalization and extensions to the Chamfer distance are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the applicability of their method in point cloud upsampling and shape synthesis, which are topics commonly studied in neural networks (cs.NE).
